13-14 May - Detroit Frosting

- 1   cup milk (split into 3/4 and 1/4 cup)
- 3   heaping tablespoon cornstarch
- 1   cup sugar
- 1   stick margarine or butter, softened
- 1/2 cup crisco
- 1   tablespoon vanilla

Make a pudding with 3/4 cup milk and 1 cup sugar over medium heat in a saucepan. In the meantime add the cornstarch to the reserved 1/4 cup milk, add to heated milk and stir until thickened as a pudding. Cool thoroughly. Beat softened margarine and crisco together, add the tablespoon of vanilla and the cold pudding mix. Mix until fluffy and light. You can add cool whip or whipped cream to this for a different flavor. 